First Team: The team that plays first (home or away depending on venue)
Opponent Team: The opposing team in the match
Venue: Location of the match (Determines whetehr is Home or Away)
Result: The Match result (W represents Win, L represents Loss and D represents Draw)
GF (goals for): Number of goals scored by the First Team
GA (goals against): Number of goals scored by the Opponent Team
CrdY: Number of yellow cards of the First Team
CrdR: Number of red cards of the First Team
2CrdY: Number of second yellow cards leading to expulsion
Fls (fouls committed): Number of fouls committed by the First team
Fld (fouls drawn): Number of fouls comitted by the Opponent team
Off (offsides): Number of offsides by the First team
Crs (crosses): Number of crosses made by the First team (Pass the ball from the side of the field into the Opponent's penalty area)
Int (interceptions): Number of interceptions made by the First team (A team successfully disrupts the Opponent's passing)
TklW (tackles won): Number of tackles won by the team (A team successfully regains possession of the ball)
Pkwon (penalty kicks won): Number of penalty kicks won by the First team
Pkcon (penalty kicks conceded): Number of penalty kicks won by the Opponent team
OG (own goals): Number of own goals scored (First team accidentally scores a goal against themselves)
Recov (ball recoveries): Number of ball recoveries (A team successfully regains possession of the ball after it has been lost or when it is loose)
Won (aerials won): Number of aerial duels won by the First team
Lost: Number of aerial duels lost by the First team
Won%: Percentage of aerial duels won by the First team
xG (expected goals): Expected goals based on shot quality
Poss (possession): Possession percentage of the First team
Attendance: Number of spectators in the match
Referee Hometown: Hometown or region of the referee
First Team Region: home or away depending on venue
